# .trivyignore — Documented risk acceptances
#
# Each suppression below is an explicit architectural decision, not a blanket
# ignore. See docs/architecture/ for the relevant ADRs.
#
# Format: <AVD-ID or CVE-ID>  # reason

# KSV106 — Container capabilities must only include NET_BIND_SERVICE
# Our deployment drops ALL capabilities already; this check flags the absence
# of an explicit `add: []` list. Runtime default without NET_RAW is equivalent.
# Risk: LOW — all capabilities are dropped, attack surface is minimal.
AVD-KSV-0106

# DS026 — Do not use the :latest tag
# The Dockerfile itself does not reference :latest; the deployment.yml image
# field uses :latest as a placeholder replaced by the release pipeline with a
# pinned digest. Trivy sees the YAML literal, not the runtime value.
# Risk: Accepted — actual deployments always use digest references.
AVD-DS-0026
